              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\nJason has just moved to a new house. He loves it, especially the big **garden**. But right now he has **boxes** piled up in almost every **room**. He needs some help **putting away** his things and **getting organized** so he has asked a couple friends to **come over** today.\n\nJason acaba de mudarse a una nueva casa. Le encanta, especialmente el gran jardín. Pero ahora mismo tiene cajas amontonadas en casi cada habitación. Necesita un poco de ayuda para guardar sus cosas y organizarse así que ha pedido a un par de amigos que vinieran hoy.\n\n> **Example:** I'm Jason and I just moved to a new house.\n\n> **Example:** I'm Sam.\n\n> **Example:** I'm Peter.\n\n---\n\n## Diálogo\n\n> **Example:** Hi guys! How are you?\n\n> **Example:** Good. How about you?\n\n> **Example:** Fine. Just a bit **tired**.\n\n> **Example:** Wow! I really like your new house. What a cool **neighborhood**!\n\n> **Example:** Yeah, thanks. I'm **looking forward** to going to the cafés and riding my bike along the lake. The house just needs a **fresh coat of paint** in most rooms.\n\n> **Example:** So, what can we do to help?\n\n> **Example:** First, I need to carry this **bed upstairs**.\n\n> **Example:** I can help you. This bed is a lot **bigger than** mine.\n\n> **Example:** I used to have a single bed but in this new house I have a much bigger **bedroom** so I bought this bigger one.\n\n> **Example:** Is there something I can do?\n\n> **Example:** I can't **reach** that **shelf**. You're **taller than** me. Can you put this picture up there?\n\n> **Example:** Of course!\n\n---\n\n***In the kitchen…***\n\n> **Example:** Where do you want me to put these **plates**?\n\n> **Example:** In that **cabinet**.\n\n> **Example:** And in which **drawer** should I put these **tablecloths**?\n\n> **Example:** You can put them in this one.\n\n> **Example:** This **kitchen** is much more **spacious** than your old one.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I'm going to do a lot more cooking here.\n\n---\n\n***Later on…***\n\n> **Example:** It's already 3 o'clock. I've got to go to work.\n\n> **Example:** And I need to meet my mom in about half an hour.\n\n> **Example:** Thanks a million for your help today! I'll buy you two dinner this weekend.\n\n> **Example:** Sounds great!\n\n> **Example:** Are you free on Saturday **evening**?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, after 6 pm.\n\n> **Example:** I'm free all day Saturday.\n\n> **Example:** Perfect. Let's meet at 6:30 pm here on Saturday and we'll walk to one of the restaurants nearby.\n\n> **Example:** Fantastic!\n\n> **Example:** Okay, thanks! See you then.",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\nJason has just moved to a new house. He loves it, especially the big **garden**. But right now he has **boxes** piled up in almost every **room**. He needs some help **putting away** his things and **getting organized** so he has asked a couple friends to **come over** today.<br>\n\n> **Example:** I'm Jason and I just moved to a new house.\n\n> **Example:** I'm Sam.\n\n> **Example:** I'm Peter.\n\n---\n\n## Dialogue\n\n> **Example:** Hi guys! How are you?\n\n> **Example:** Good. How about you?\n\n> **Example:** Fine. Just a bit **tired**.\n\n> **Example:** Wow! I really like your new house. What a cool **neighborhood**!\n\n> **Example:** Yeah, thanks. I'm **looking forward** to going to the cafés and riding my bike along the lake. The house just needs a **fresh coat of paint** in most rooms.\n\n> **Example:** So, what can we do to help?\n\n> **Example:** First, I need to carry this **bed upstairs**.\n\n> **Example:** I can help you. This bed is a lot **bigger than** mine.\n\n> **Example:** I used to have a single bed but in this new house I have a much bigger **bedroom** so I bought this bigger one.\n\n> **Example:** Is there something I can do?\n\n> **Example:** I can't **reach** that **shelf**. You're **taller than** me. Can you put this picture up there?\n\n> **Example:** Of course!\n\n---\n\n***In the kitchen…***\n\n> **Example:** Where do you want me to put these **plates**?\n\n> **Example:** In that **cabinet**.\n\n> **Example:** And in which **drawer** should I put these **tablecloths**?\n\n> **Example:** You can put them in this one.\n\n> **Example:** This **kitchen** is much more **spacious** than your old one.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I'm going to do a lot more cooking here.\n\n---\n\n***Later on…***\n\n> **Example:** It's already 3 o'clock. I've got to go to work.\n\n> **Example:** And I need to meet my mom in about half an hour.\n\n> **Example:** Thanks a million for your help today! I'll buy you two dinner this weekend.\n\n> **Example:** Sounds great!\n\n> **Example:** Are you free on Saturday **evening**?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, after 6 pm.\n\n> **Example:** I'm free all day Saturday.\n\n> **Example:** Perfect. Let's meet at 6:30 pm here on Saturday and we'll walk to one of the restaurants nearby.\n\n> **Example:** Fantastic!\n\n> **Example:** Okay, thanks! See you then."
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 273,
              "order": 2,
              "slug": {
                "es": "jobs",
                "en": "jobs"
