              "display": {
                "es": "Los trabajos",
                "en": "Jobs"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\nChristina is a 22 year old woman and she is **currently unemployed**. Today she is at her friend John's house and they are talking about the different jobs she has had and ways to find work.\n\nChristina es una mujer de 22 años y actualmente está sin trabajo. Hoy está en la casa de su amigo John y están hablando de los diferentes trabajos que ha tenido y maneras de encontrar trabajo.\n\n## Diálogo\n\n> **Example:** So, tell me about your last job.\n\n> **Example:** Well, last summer I was working as a **waitress** in an Italian restaurant.\n\n> **Example:** Did you like it?\n\n> **Example:** I enjoyed working with people. I would chat with the **customers** and I got some great **tips**, but then my **boss** got angry at me.\n\n> **Example:** What happened?\n\n> **Example:** He said that I **wasn't serving** the food quick enough. I tried to work **more quickly** but I wasn't as fast as the other servers. At the end of the summer he told me that he couldn't **renew** my **contract**.\n\n> **Example:** Oh, that's too bad. Well, what other work have you done?\n\n> **Example:** I worked as a **receptionist** in a gym a few years ago.\n\n> **Example:** What did you like about that job?\n\n> **Example:** The **environment** at the gym was good, but I didn't really like working at a **desk**.\n\n> **Example:** You had to answer phone calls, didn't you?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, that part was okay, but I didn't like **filing** and all the **paperwork**.\n\n> **Example:** Let's look at this website to see what job ads there are.\n\n> **Example:** Okay, great idea!\n\n> **Example:** Here is a **position** as a **secretary** in a school. This position involves **meetings**, maintaining **office supplies** and some filing.\n\n> **Example:** I don't know. I don't like **office work**.\n\n> **Example:** Here is another one. This is a **shop assistant** position.\n\n> **Example:** I'm interested in that one! I worked in a **clothing shop** one summer. I really enjoyed it!\n\n> **Example:** Do you want to send your **c.v.**?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, but I need to **update** it first.\n\n> **Example:** I can help you.\n\n> **Example:** Thank you. How's your job?\n\n> **Example:** Pretty good. My dad is a **designer** and I've always been interested in **art and design**. I studied **graphic design** at university. Now I'm working at a graphic design firm.\n\n> **Example:** That's fantastic!\n\n> **Example:** I'm only in my 3rd month there so I mostly do filing and **administrative tasks**, but in 6 months I will be designing some projects.",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\nChristina is a 22 year old woman and she is **currently unemployed**. Today she is at her friend John's house and they are talking about the different jobs she has had and ways to find work.\n\n## Dialogue\n\n> **Example:** So, tell me about your last job.\n\n> **Example:** Well, last summer I was working as a **waitress** in an Italian restaurant.\n\n> **Example:** Did you like it?\n\n> **Example:** I enjoyed working with people. I would chat with the **customers** and I got some great **tips**, but then my **boss** got angry at me.\n\n> **Example:** What happened?\n\n> **Example:** He said that I **wasn't serving** the food quick enough. I tried to work **more quickly** but I wasn't as fast as the other servers. At the end of the summer he told me that he couldn't **renew** my **contract**.\n\n> **Example:** Oh, that's too bad. Well, what other work have you done?\n\n> **Example:** I worked as a **receptionist** in a gym a few years ago.\n\n> **Example:** What did you like about that job?\n\n> **Example:** The **environment** at the gym was good, but I didn't really like working at a **desk**.\n\n> **Example:** You had to answer phone calls, didn't you?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, that part was okay, but I didn't like **filing** and all the **paperwork**.\n\n> **Example:** Let's look at this website to see what job ads there are.\n\n> **Example:** Okay, great idea!\n\n> **Example:** Here is a **position** as a **secretary** in a school. This position involves **meetings**, maintaining **office supplies** and some filing.\n\n> **Example:** I don't know. I don't like **office work**.\n\n> **Example:** Here is another one. This is a **shop assistant** position.\n\n> **Example:** I'm interested in that one! I worked in a **clothing shop** one summer. I really enjoyed it!\n\n> **Example:** Do you want to send your **c.v.**?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, but I need to **update** it first.\n\n> **Example:** I can help you.\n\n> **Example:** Thank you. How's your job?\n\n> **Example:** Pretty good. My dad is a **designer** and I've always been interested in **art and design**. I studied **graphic design** at university. Now I'm working at a graphic design firm.\n\n> **Example:** That's fantastic!\n\n> **Example:** I'm only in my 3rd month there so I mostly do filing and **administrative tasks**, but in 6 months I will be designing some projects."
              }
