              "display": {
                "es": "Viajar",
                "en": "Traveling"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\nJim is very excited about his plans for this summer and he is telling his friend Rachel all about them.\n\nJim está muy emocionado con sus planes para este verano y está explicándoselos a su amiga Rachel.\n\n## Diálogo\n\n> **Example:** Hi Rachel!\n\n> **Example:** Hi Jim! How are you?\n\n> **Example:** I'm **really excited**! I'm preparing a **trip** to Europe this summer.\n\n> **Example:** That sounds fantastic! Who are you going to travel with?\n\n> **Example:** With my cousin Sam. We both have a month off so we are going to **backpack** across Europe together.\n\n> **Example:** How old is Sam?\n\n> **Example:** We're the same age.\n\n> **Example:** Perfect! You're going to travel by train, **aren't you**?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, that's right!\n\n> **Example:** **Which countries** are you going to visit?\n\n> **Example:** We hope to go to Spain, France and Italy.\n\n> **Example:** And where are you going to **stay**?\n\n> **Example:** We'll be staying in **youth hostels**. We **can't afford** to stay in hotels.\n\n> **Example:** Yeah, youth hostels are usually **clean** and **inexpensive**.\n\n> **Example:** Also, Sam's friend from university who is studying in Madrid has offered to put us up in her apartment for a few days.\n\n> **Example:** That's cool! You can speak Spanish, **can't you**?\n\n> **Example:** Not really. But Sam speaks really **well**.\n\n> **Example:** Do you speak any other **languages**?\n\n> **Example:** I took French in high school, but I only have a basic level.\n\n> **Example:** That's okay. There's always someone who speaks English.\n\n> **Example:** I think that's the case in big cities and tourist areas, but not in small villages.\n\n> **Example:** That's true.\n\n> **Example:** **Anyway**, I have to go to work. Great to see you!\n\n> **Example:** You too. Have a fantastic trip!\n\n> **Example:** Look at my pictures on Instagram!\n\n> **Example:** Okay, I will!",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\nJim is very excited about his plans for this summer and he is telling his friend Rachel all about them.\n\n## Dialogue\n\n> **Example:** Hi Rachel!\n\n> **Example:** Hi Jim! How are you?\n\n> **Example:** I'm **really excited**! I'm preparing a **trip** to Europe this summer.\n\n> **Example:** That sounds fantastic! Who are you going to travel with?\n\n> **Example:** With my cousin Sam. We both have a month off so we are going to **backpack** across Europe together.\n\n> **Example:** How old is Sam?\n\n> **Example:** We're the same age.\n\n> **Example:** Perfect! You're going to travel by train, **aren't you**?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, that's right!\n\n> **Example:** **Which countries** are you going to visit?\n\n> **Example:** We hope to go to Spain, France and Italy.\n\n> **Example:** And where are you going to **stay**?\n\n> **Example:** We'll be staying in **youth hostels**. We **can't afford** to stay in hotels.\n\n> **Example:** Yeah, youth hostels are usually **clean** and **inexpensive**.\n\n> **Example:** Also, Sam's friend from university who is studying in Madrid has offered to put us up in her apartment for a few days.\n\n> **Example:** That's cool! You can speak Spanish, **can't you**?\n\n> **Example:** Not really. But Sam speaks really **well**.\n\n> **Example:** Do you speak any other **languages**?\n\n> **Example:** I took French in high school, but I only have a basic level.\n\n> **Example:** That's okay. There's always someone who speaks English.\n\n> **Example:** I think that's the case in big cities and tourist areas, but not in small villages.\n\n> **Example:** That's true.\n\n> **Example:** **Anyway**, I have to go to work. Great to see you!\n\n> **Example:** You too. Have a fantastic trip!\n\n> **Example:** Look at my pictures on Instagram!\n\n> **Example:** Okay, I will!"
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 275,
              "order": 4,
              "slug": {
                "es": "at-the-restaurant",
                "en": "at-the-restaurant"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "En el restaurante",
                "en": "At the Restaurant"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\n> **Example:** The Smith family went to a restaurant a few months ago to celebrate Dad's birthday. They were enjoying their meal very much until something strange happened.<br>\n\nLa familia Smith fue a un restaurante hace unos meses para celebrar el cumpleaños de papá. Estaban disfrutando mucho de su cena hasta que algo extraño pasó.\n\n---\n\nThe family climbed out of the car and walked slowly into the restaurant. Dad was in a very good **mood** because it was his 60th birthday that day. He used to hate celebrating his **birthday**, but now that he's older he enjoys the **attention**.\n\nIt was very hot that night, possibly **the hottest** night of the year. They all chose to go to the **Fish and Seafood** restaurant in their village. It had **air-conditioning** so it wouldn't be as hot as at home.\n\nWhen they sat down the **waiter** came quickly to bring them the **menus**. He told them about the **specials** that evening and gave them some time to decide what they wanted to **order**. Mom ordered salmon, Luke ordered shrimp and Dad decided to have something special… lobster.\n\nThey started their **meal** with some nice salads and delicious, crispy bread with olive oil. They were talking about the rest of their summer holidays. Then the **main courses** arrived. They all smelled **absolutely** fantastic.Then suddenly Dad saw something **strange**.The lobster on his plate was still moving its claws. He was **shocked**!\n\nThe waiter came over immediately and picked up the plate with the moving lobster. He brought it back to the kitchen and came back to the table a few minutes later with another plate of lobster. After **apologizing** he offered to give him the lobster for free.\n\nEven though Dad was surprised by what had happened he ate his lobster hungrily and was happy to get a free meal on his birthday.",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\n> **Example:** The Smith family went to a restaurant a few months ago to celebrate Dad's birthday. They were enjoying their meal very much until something strange happened.\n\n---\n\nThe family climbed out of the car and walked slowly into the restaurant. Dad was in a very good **mood** because it was his 60th birthday that day. He used to hate celebrating his **birthday**, but now that he's older he enjoys the **attention**.\n\nIt was very hot that night, possibly **the hottest** night of the year. They all chose to go to the **Fish and Seafood** restaurant in their village. It had **air-conditioning** so it wouldn't be as hot as at home.\n\nWhen they sat down the **waiter** came quickly to bring them the **menus**. He told them about the **specials** that evening and gave them some time to decide what they wanted to **order**. Mom ordered salmon, Luke ordered shrimp and Dad decided to have something special… lobster.\n\nThey started their **meal** with some nice salads and delicious, crispy bread with olive oil. They were talking about the rest of their summer holidays. Then the **main courses** arrived. They all smelled **absolutely** fantastic.Then suddenly Dad saw something **strange**.The lobster on his plate was still moving its claws. He was **shocked**!\n\nThe waiter came over immediately and picked up the plate with the moving lobster. He brought it back to the kitchen and came back to the table a few minutes later with another plate of lobster. After **apologizing** he offered to give him the lobster for free.\n\nEven though Dad was surprised by what had happened he ate his lobster hungrily and was happy to get a free meal on his birthday."
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 276,
              "order": 5,
              "slug": {
