              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\nHenry and his family have arrived at the hotel where they will stay for 2 nights. Here is the conversation that Henry has with the hotel receptionist. Although the room is not what Henry was expecting, the receptionist offers him a solution.\n\nHenry y su familia han llegado al hotel donde van a alojarse por 2 noches. Aquí está la conversación que tiene Henry con la recepcionista. Aunque la habitación no es lo que Henry esperaba, la recepcionista le ofrece una solución.\n\n## Diálogo\n\n> **Example:** Good afternoon. Can I help you?\n\n> **Example:** Hello. I have a **reservation** for a **quadruple room**.\n\n> **Example:** What's your name, please?\n\n> **Example:** Henry Samson.\n\n> **Example:** You made your reservation online, didn't you?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I did.\n\n> **Example:** First I will need your **driver's license** or **passport**, please.\n\n> **Example:** Here you go.\n\n> **Example:** Please **sign** here and I will show you to your room.\n\n> **Example:** Great, thank you.\n\n> **Example:** This is it. Room 212. Here is your **room key**.\n\n> **Example:** Oh, it's very small. I don't think this will be big enough for my wife and I and our 2 children. Have you got any bigger rooms for four?\n\n> **Example:** No, but you could stay in two rooms that have an **adjoining** door.\n\n> **Example:** That would probably be better. Could you show me them?\n\n> **Example:** Of course. Here they are.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, these two rooms have a lot **more space**.\n\n> **Example:** If you would like to stay in these rooms we will have to go back down to **reception** to change your reservation.\n\n> **Example:** Of course.\n\n> **Example:** The two rooms for two nights will be $320. That is only $50 more than the quadruple one.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, that sounds fine.\n\n> **Example:** Please sign here. And here are your two room keys.\n\n> **Example:** Thank you. What time is **breakfast** served?\n\n> **Example:** From 7 o'clock to 10 o'clock in our **dining room** at the end of this **hall**.\n\n> **Example:** Great. Is it a buffet breakfast or do we order off the menu?\n\n> **Example:** It's a buffet breakfast, there are many hot and cold dishes served.\n\n> **Example:** Wonderful!\n\n> **Example:** Have a very nice stay.\n\n> **Example:** Thank you!",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\nHenry and his family have arrived at the hotel where they will stay for 2 nights. Here is the conversation that Henry has with the hotel receptionist. Although the room is not what Henry was expecting, the receptionist offers him a solution.\n\n## Dialogue\n\n> **Example:** Good afternoon. Can I help you?\n\n> **Example:** Hello. I have a **reservation** for a **quadruple room**.\n\n> **Example:** What's your name, please?\n\n> **Example:** Henry Samson.\n\n> **Example:** You made your reservation online, didn't you?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I did.\n\n> **Example:** First I will need your **driver's license** or **passport**, please.\n\n> **Example:** Here you go.\n\n> **Example:** Please **sign** here and I will show you to your room.\n\n> **Example:** Great, thank you.\n\n> **Example:** This is it. Room 212. Here is your **room key**.\n\n> **Example:** Oh, it's very small. I don't think this will be big enough for my wife and I and our 2 children. Have you got any bigger rooms for four?\n\n> **Example:** No, but you could stay in two rooms that have an **adjoining** door.\n\n> **Example:** That would probably be better. Could you show me them?\n\n> **Example:** Of course. Here they are.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, these two rooms have a lot **more space**.\n\n> **Example:** If you would like to stay in these rooms we will have to go back down to **reception** to change your reservation.\n\n> **Example:** Of course.\n\n> **Example:** The two rooms for two nights will be $320. That is only $50 more than the quadruple one.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, that sounds fine.\n\n> **Example:** Please sign here. And here are your two room keys.\n\n> **Example:** Thank you. What time is **breakfast** served?\n\n> **Example:** From 7 o'clock to 10 o'clock in our **dining room** at the end of this **hall**.\n\n> **Example:** Great. Is it a buffet breakfast or do we order off the menu?\n\n> **Example:** It's a buffet breakfast, there are many hot and cold dishes served.\n\n> **Example:** Wonderful!\n\n> **Example:** Have a very nice stay.\n\n> **Example:** Thank you!"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
