            {
              "code": 277,
              "order": 1,
              "slug": {
                "es": "at-the-doctor-s-office",
                "en": "at-the-doctor-s-office"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "En el médico",
                "en": "At the Doctor's Office"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\nAndrew is waiting at the doctor’s office. He is there for two reasons today. Find out what the Doctor recommends.\n\nAndrew está esperando en la consulta de su doctor. Está allí por dos razones hoy. Averigua lo que el doctor le recomienda.\n\n## Diálogo\n\n> **Example:** Hello, Andrew. **What's the matter**?\n\n> **Example:** Well, I'm here for two reasons. These last few days I have had a very **sore throat**. I can **hardly swallow** and I have had **high fevers**.\n\n> **Example:** Let me take a look at your throat. Open please.\n\n> **Example:** Okay.\n\n> **Example:** It looks like a bad throat **infection**. I am going to **prescribe antibiotics**. You will have to take the **pills** for 7 days.\n\n> **Example:** All right.\n\n> **Example:** You should take one pill every 8 hours. Please don't forget to take them. Also you must finish the full 7 day **treatment**. If you don't, you might not **get rid of** the infection and it could **come back**.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I will.\n\n> **Example:** What else is wrong?\n\n> **Example:** I have been having a lot of **pain** in my left **knee** lately.\n\n> **Example:** Have you been doing any sort of **exercise**?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I started running about 2 months ago. I have been running between 5 and 10 km a day.\n\n> **Example:** Did you **fall** or do any **harsh movement** recently?\n\n> **Example:** No, that's what is so strange.\n\n> **Example:** Where does it **hurt**?\n\n> **Example:** On the side of my knee… here.\n\n> **Example:** Let me move your leg around and see….does this hurt?\n\n> **Example:** Yes! Ouch!\n\n> **Example:** And does it hurt if I **bend** your knee like this?\n\n> **Example:** Not so much, just a little.\n\n> **Example:** It looks like a **ligament injury**. You should rest your knee for about a week. Put ice pads on it a few times a day and wear this knee **brace** when you walk.\n\n> **Example:** Okay. I wanted to run in a 10 kilometer race in about 6 weeks. Should I do it?\n\n> **Example:** I wouldn't put too much pressure on your knee. Make an appointment for about 2 weeks from now and we'll see how it looks.\n\n> **Example:** Okay. Thank you, Doctor.\n\n> **Example:** You're welcome.",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\nAndrew is waiting at the doctor’s office. He is there for two reasons today. Find out what the Doctor recommends.\n\n## Dialogue\n\n> **Example:** Hello, Andrew. **What's the matter**?\n\n> **Example:** Well, I'm here for two reasons. These last few days I have had a very **sore throat**. I can **hardly swallow** and I have had **high fevers**.\n\n> **Example:** Let me take a look at your throat. Open please.\n\n> **Example:** Okay.\n\n> **Example:** It looks like a bad throat **infection**. I am going to **prescribe antibiotics**. You will have to take the **pills** for 7 days.\n\n> **Example:** All right.\n\n> **Example:** You should take one pill every 8 hours. Please don't forget to take them. Also you must finish the full 7 day **treatment**. If you don't, you might not **get rid of** the infection and it could **come back**.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I will.\n\n> **Example:** What else is wrong?\n\n> **Example:** I have been having a lot of **pain** in my left **knee** lately.\n\n> **Example:** Have you been doing any sort of **exercise**?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I started running about 2 months ago. I have been running between 5 and 10 km a day.\n\n> **Example:** Did you **fall** or do any **harsh movement** recently?\n\n> **Example:** No, that's what is so strange.\n\n> **Example:** Where does it **hurt**?\n\n> **Example:** On the side of my knee… here.\n\n> **Example:** Let me move your leg around and see….does this hurt?\n\n> **Example:** Yes! Ouch!\n\n> **Example:** And does it hurt if I **bend** your knee like this?\n\n> **Example:** Not so much, just a little.\n\n> **Example:** It looks like a **ligament injury**. You should rest your knee for about a week. Put ice pads on it a few times a day and wear this knee **brace** when you walk.\n\n> **Example:** Okay. I wanted to run in a 10 kilometer race in about 6 weeks. Should I do it?\n\n> **Example:** I wouldn't put too much pressure on your knee. Make an appointment for about 2 weeks from now and we'll see how it looks.\n\n> **Example:** Okay. Thank you, Doctor.\n\n> **Example:** You're welcome."
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 278,
              "order": 2,
              "slug": {
                "es": "at-the-bank",
                "en": "at-the-bank"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "En el banco",
                "en": "At the Bank"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\nJessica and Lewis are a **young couple** and they are interested in buying their first home. They **just got married** two months ago and they have been looking at houses for sale for the last few weeks. This week they found the **perfect home**, but will they be able to get a **mortgage** from the **bank** to buy it? Mrs. Simmons works at the bank and she informs them.\n\nJessica y Lewis son una pareja joven y están interesados en comprar su primera casa. Se acaban de casar hace dos meses y las últimas semanas han estado mirando casas en venta. Esta semana han encontrado la casa perfecta, ¿pero podrán conseguir una hipoteca del banco para comprarla? Sra. Simmons trabaja en el banco y les informa.\n\n## Diálogo\n\n> **Example:** Good morning. I'm Lewis.\n\n> **Example:** Hello Lewis, Jessica. Nice to meet you both. I'm Mrs. Simmons.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, same to you.\n\n> **Example:** So tell me about the house you found.\n\n> **Example:** It's an old home that needs to be **renovated** but it's in a fantastic **family-friendly neighborhood**. It's on Maple Street. And the price is great!\n\n> **Example:** What is their **asking price**?\n\n> **Example:** $220,000, but the **realtor** says we can probably get it down to $200,000.\n\n> **Example:** That is a good price for that neighborhood. You will need extra **funds** for the renovation, won't you?\n\n> **Example:** No, my father and uncle have a **family business** in **home renovation** and we have some **savings** so we won't need any extra money.\n\n> **Example:** Okay, great. We can offer you a **low-interest rate mortgage**.\n\n> **Example:** What is **required** to get the mortgage?\n\n> **Example:** You need to bring me a copy of your last **paychecks** and **tax returns** and we'll have to check your **credit history**.\n\n> **Example:** Is there anything else that we'll need?\n\n> **Example:** The house will need to be **valued** and you must **open an account** at our bank.\n\n> **Example:** Okay, I will prepare those documents and bring them to you next week.\n\n> **Example:** Great. See you next week. If you have any questions, here is my **business card**.",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\nJessica and Lewis are a **young couple** and they are interested in buying their first home. They **just got married** two months ago and they have been looking at houses for sale for the last few weeks. This week they found the **perfect home**, but will they be able to get a **mortgage** from the **bank** to buy it? Mrs. Simmons works at the bank and she informs them.\n\n## Dialogue\n\n> **Example:** Good morning. I'm Lewis.\n\n> **Example:** Hello Lewis, Jessica. Nice to meet you both. I'm Mrs. Simmons.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, same to you.\n\n> **Example:** So tell me about the house you found.\n\n> **Example:** It's an old home that needs to be **renovated** but it's in a fantastic **family-friendly neighborhood**. It's on Maple Street. And the price is great!\n\n> **Example:** What is their **asking price**?\n\n> **Example:** $220,000, but the **realtor** says we can probably get it down to $200,000.\n\n> **Example:** That is a good price for that neighborhood. You will need extra **funds** for the renovation, won't you?\n\n> **Example:** No, my father and uncle have a **family business** in **home renovation** and we have some **savings** so we won't need any extra money.\n\n> **Example:** Okay, great. We can offer you a **low-interest rate mortgage**.\n\n> **Example:** What is **required** to get the mortgage?\n\n> **Example:** You need to bring me a copy of your last **paychecks** and **tax returns** and we'll have to check your **credit history**.\n\n> **Example:** Is there anything else that we'll need?\n\n> **Example:** The house will need to be **valued** and you must **open an account** at our bank.\n\n> **Example:** Okay, I will prepare those documents and bring them to you next week.\n\n> **Example:** Great. See you next week. If you have any questions, here is my **business card**."
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 279,
              "order": 3,
              "slug": {
                "es": "at-the-market",
                "en": "at-the-market"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "En el mercado",
                "en": "At the Market"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\nJohn and Chris are at a great **street market** today. There are so many **stands** of interesting products, from **antiques**, **jewelry** and **collectibles** to **hand-made clothing**, food and even small **pets**.\n\nJohn y Chris están en un buen mercado callejero hoy. Hay tantas paradas de productos interesantes, desde antigüedades, joyas y coleccionables hasta ropa hecha a mano, comida y incluso pequeños animales domésticos.\n\n## Diálogo\n\n> **Example:** Look at that stand, Chris. There are some old **records**!\n\n> **Example:** Yeah, a lot of people are collecting records again.\n\n> **Example:** Wow! Here is the first **album** by U2. I would love to **own** this!\n\n> **Example:** Pretty cool! How much is this?\n\n> **Example:** This one is very special. There are only a **few copies left**. It's $25.\n\n> **Example:** Twenty-five dollars? I'll give you $15 for it.\n\n> **Example:** Sorry, I can't **go lower** than $22.\n\n> **Example:** Come on…. how about $20?\n\n> **Example:** Okay, but that's **the lowest** I will go. Would you like me to **wrap** it?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, please **or else** it will get scratched in my bag.\n\n---\n\n***A little bit later…***\n\n> **Example:** I would like to go look at those antique clocks and watches. My Dad's birthday **is coming up** and he loves antiques.\n\n> **Example:** Okay, let's go over there.\n\n> **Example:** This watch is gorgeous. I think my Dad would love this.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, it's nice. Do you think it works?\n\n> **Example:** How old is this watch?\n\n**Vendor**\n\n> **Example:** It's 40 years old.\n\n> **Example:** Where was it made?\n\n> **Example:** In Switzerland. It's a very good piece.\n\n> **Example:** Does it work?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, of course. It just needs a new battery.\n\n> **Example:** Do you have one so we can check?\n\n> **Example:** Sure, I will show you.\n\n> **Example:** My Dad already has two other watches, but **neither** of them works so he doesn't wear **either** of them lately.\n\n> **Example:** I bet you he would be very happy with this.\n\n> **Example:** How much is it?\n\n> **Example:** $100.\n\n> **Example:** I don't have enough money. Can't you sell it to me for less?\n\n> **Example:** No. This piece is a **high-quality** Swiss watch.\n\n> **Example:** How about $75?\n\n> **Example:** Sorry. I can't go lower than $100 **I'm afraid**.\n\n> **Example:** Oh well, that's too bad. I can't afford it. Thank you either way.\n\n> **Example:** Have you seen this watch? It's in your **price range**.\n\n> **Example:** It's nice, but I don't think my Dad will like it. Thanks anyway.\n\n> **Example:** Have a nice day!",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\nJohn and Chris are at a great **street market** today. There are so many **stands** of interesting products, from **antiques**, **jewelry** and **collectibles** to **hand-made clothing**, food and even small **pets**.\n\n## Dialogue\n\n> **Example:** Look at that stand, Chris. There are some old **records**!\n\n> **Example:** Yeah, a lot of people are collecting records again.\n\n> **Example:** Wow! Here is the first **album** by U2. I would love to **own** this!\n\n> **Example:** Pretty cool! How much is this?\n\n**Vendor:**\n\n> **Example:** This one is very special. There are only a **few copies left**. It's $25.\n\n> **Example:** Twenty-five dollars? I will give you $15 for it.\n\n> **Example:** Sorry, I can't **go lower** than $22.\n\n> **Example:** Come on…. how about $20?\n\n> **Example:** Okay, but that's **the lowest** I will go. Would you like me to **wrap** it?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, please **or else** it will get scratched in my bag.\n\n---\n\n***A little bit later…***\n\n> **Example:** I would like to go look at those antique clocks and watches. My Dad's birthday **is coming up** and he loves antiques.\n\n> **Example:** Okay, let's go over there.\n\n> **Example:** This watch is gorgeous. I think my Dad would love this.\n\n> **Example:** Yes, it's nice. Do you think it works?\n\n> **Example:** How old is this watch?\n\n**Vendor:**\n\n> **Example:** It's 40 years old.\n\n> **Example:** Where was it made?\n\n> **Example:** In Switzerland. It's a very good piece.\n\n> **Example:** Does it work?\n\n> **Example:** Yes, of course. It just needs a new battery.\n\n> **Example:** Do you have one so we can check?\n\n> **Example:** Sure, I will show you.\n\n> **Example:** My Dad already has two other watches, but **neither** of them works so he doesn't wear **either** of them lately.\n\n> **Example:** I bet you he would be very happy with this.\n\n> **Example:** How much is it?\n\n> **Example:** $100.\n\n> **Example:** I don't have enough money. Can't you sell it to me for less?\n\n> **Example:** No. This piece is a **high-quality** Swiss watch.\n\n> **Example:** How about $75?\n\n> **Example:** Sorry. I can't go lower than $100 **I'm afraid**.\n\n> **Example:** Oh well, that's too bad. I can't afford it. Thank you either way.\n\n> **Example:** Have you seen this watch? It's in your **price range**.\n\n> **Example:** It's nice, but I don't think my Dad will like it. Thanks anyway.\n\n> **Example:** Have a nice day!"
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 280,
              "order": 4,
              "slug": {
                "es": "a-mystery",
                "en": "a-mystery"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "Un misterio",
                "en": "A Mystery"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\n> **Example:** Amy and James are enjoying themselves at a campsite until something mysterious and unfortunate happens. How will they resolve it?<br>\n\nAmy y James están disfrutándose en un camping hasta que algo misterioso y desafortunado ocurre. ¿Cómo lo arreglarán?\n\n---\n\nIt was a **warm** summer night and James and I were staying at a **campsite** near the sea. We had chosen that campsite **due to the fact** that our friend Jessica had stayed there and had **recommended** it.\n\nAfter a lovely day at the beach **dipping** in the sea, **sunbathing** and playing beach volleyball we arrived at the campsite feeling quite relaxed, but **incredibly** hungry. We **hurriedly** prepared ourselves a delicious bowl of sliced fruit and some biscuits. Afterwards we **grabbed** our towels and **toiletries** and walked to the showers.\n\nWe came back after only about 20 minutes. As we **approached** the **tent** something **seemed** different.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Example:** Did we leave the tent door **wide open**, Amy?\n\n> **Example:** No!\n\n<br>\n\nWe **peeked** our heads inside the tent and saw that **someone had stolen** our bicycles.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Example:** Oh no!\n\n> **Example:** We made a mistake. We should have locked them up!\n\n> **Example:** It **must've been** some kids around here. We've only been gone about 15 to 20 minutes.\n\n> **Example:** They **can't have gone far**.\n\n<br>\n\nWe asked the people staying in the next **plot** if they had seen anyone taking anything from our tent. They said that they hadn't but that they had been at the swimming pool most of the last hour. We walked around the **whole** campsite, but there was **no sign** of our bikes.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Example:** I'll go speak with someone in reception.\n\n> **Example:** Wait!\n\n> **Example:** Maybe we **should make sure** that they didn't steal anything else.\n\n<br>\n\nWe looked through all of our things and realized that some money had been stolen as well.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Example:** What a **nightmare**!\n\n<br>\n\nAfter speaking to the campsite **staff**, the local police were called to do a **police report**. We described what had been stolen from our tent, they asked us lots of questions and gave us a copy of the report.\n\nWe walked back to the tent slowly feeling **discouraged** and **annoyed**. That night we went to bed early and got up at sunrise the next morning. As we **climbed out** of our tent we saw our bicycles **leaning up** against a nearby tree! We never **found out** who had taken them or why, but we did learn that we could never leave our things in a tent again.",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\n> **Example:** Amy and James are enjoying themselves at a campsite until something mysterious and unfortunate happens. How will they resolve it?<br>\n\nAmy y James están disfrutándose en un camping hasta que algo misterioso y desafortunado ocurre. ¿Cómo lo arreglarán?\n\n---\n\nIt was a **warm** summer night and James and I were staying at a **campsite** near the sea. We had chosen that campsite **due to the fact** that our friend Jessica had stayed there and had **recommended** it.\n\nAfter a lovely day at the beach **dipping** in the sea, **sunbathing** and playing beach volleyball we arrived at the campsite feeling quite relaxed, but **incredibly** hungry. We **hurriedly** prepared ourselves a delicious bowl of sliced fruit and some biscuits. Afterwards we **grabbed** our towels and **toiletries** and walked to the showers.\n\nWe came back after only about 20 minutes. As we **approached** the **tent** something **seemed** different.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Example:** Did we leave the tent door **wide open**, Amy?\n\n> **Example:** No!\n\n<br>\n\nWe **peeked** our heads inside the tent and saw that **someone had stolen** our bicycles.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Example:** Oh no!\n\n> **Example:** We made a mistake. We should have locked them up!\n\n> **Example:** It **must've been** some kids around here. We've only been gone about 15 to 20 minutes.\n\n> **Example:** They **can't have gone far**.\n\n<br>\n\nWe asked the people staying in the next **plot** if they had seen anyone taking anything from our tent. They said that they hadn't but that they had been at the swimming pool most of the last hour. We walked around the **whole** campsite, but there was **no sign** of our bikes.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Example:** I'll go speak with someone in reception.\n\n> **Example:** Wait!\n\n> **Example:** Maybe we **should make sure** that they didn't steal anything else.\n\n<br>\n\nWe looked through all of our things and realized that some money had been stolen as well.\n\n<br>\n\n> **Example:** What a **nightmare**!\n\n<br>\n\nAfter speaking to the campsite **staff**, the local police were called to do a **police report**. We described what had been stolen from our tent, they asked us lots of questions and gave us a copy of the report.\n\nWe walked back to the tent slowly feeling **discouraged** and **annoyed**. That night we went to bed early and got up at sunrise the next morning. As we **climbed out** of our tent we saw our bicycles **leaning up** against a nearby tree! We never **found out** who had taken them or why, but we did learn that we could never leave our things in a tent again."
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 281,
              "order": 5,
              "slug": {
                "es": "at-a-festival",
                "en": "at-a-festival"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "En un festival",
                "en": "At a Festival"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Introducción\n\nJennifer and Sam are really looking forward to the festival they are going to today. There will be a **wide variety** of different **activities**, **performances** and **food**.\n\nJennifer y Sam están esperando con ilusión la Festival que van a asistir hoy. Habrá una gran variedad de diferentes actividades, espectáculos y comida.\n\n## Diálogo\n\n> **Example:** Hi Sam. Where shall we meet today?\n\n> **Example:** How about in front of the market at one o'clock?\n\n> **Example:** Okay, perfect! See you there!\n\n---\n\n***Later…***\n\n> **Example:** Hi! What a **cool outfit**! It's so **colorful**!\n\n> **Example:** Oh thanks. My dad brought it back from one of his **business trips** in Indonesia.\n\n> **Example:** Let's go get a **timetable** of all the events today.\n\n> **Example:** Great idea!\n\n> **Example:** Here it says that there's a **magic show** in the **main square** at two o'clock, there's a **jazz concert** at 3:30 and there's a **food and wine festival** starting at 5 pm.\n\n> **Example:** Great! I'd like to do all of that!\n\n> **Example:** Me too! It looks like tickets **are sold** in that office.\n\n---\n\n***At the concert...***\n\n> **Example:** They are **such good musicians**. They **must have been rehearsing** for months.\n\n> **Example:** I agree. It's magical! They seem to **radiate happiness** with their music. Look how everyone is dancing!\n\n> **Example:** I know! It's amazing!\n\n> **Example:** I'm **getting hungry**. I **haven't eaten since** 11 this morning.\n\n> **Example:** Why don't you go buy yourself a bag of potato chips or something?\n\n> **Example:** I might, but if I leave now, the concert **will have finished by the time** I come back.\n\n> **Example:** You're right. Let's wait for the food festival. Here, I brought some sweets in my purse.\n\n> **Example:** Oh, thanks.\n\n---\n\n***At the food and wine festival...***\n\n> **Example:** I've been to this food festival before, but this year it's **so much bigger**!\n\n> **Example:** Yeah, look at all the stands!\n\n> **Example:** We can **each either** buy 3 or 6 tickets for tastes of food. The tastes are small dishes of food, so you can try lots of different dishes.\n\n> **Example:** I'm **starving**. I could eat 20 dishes!\n\n> **Example:** I think I'll just buy 3. I **would eat 6 if I weren't** on a diet.\n\n> **Example:** Come on! You only live once. Enjoy yourself!\n\n> **Example:** I guess you're right. I'll buy 6 tickets!",
                "en": "## Introduction\n\nJennifer and Sam are really looking forward to the festival they are going to today. There will be a **wide variety** of different **activities**, **performances** and **food**.\n\n## Dialogue\n\n> **Example:** Hi Sam. Where shall we meet today?\n\n> **Example:** How about in front of the market at one o'clock?\n\n> **Example:** Okay, perfect! See you there!\n\n---\n\n***Later…***\n\n> **Example:** Hi! What a **cool outfit**! It's so **colorful**!\n\n> **Example:** Oh thanks. My dad brought it back from one of his **business trips** in Indonesia.\n\n> **Example:** Let's go get a **timetable** of all the events today.\n\n> **Example:** Great idea!\n\n> **Example:** Here it says that there's a **magic show** in the **main square** at two o'clock, there's a **jazz concert** at 3:30 and there's a **food and wine festival** starting at 5 pm.\n\n> **Example:** Great! I'd like to do all of that!\n\n> **Example:** Me too! It looks like tickets **are sold** in that office.\n\n---\n\n***At the concert...***\n\n> **Example:** They are **such good musicians**. They **must have been rehearsing** for months.\n\n> **Example:** I agree. It's magical! They seem to **radiate happiness** with their music. Look how everyone is dancing!\n\n> **Example:** I know! It's amazing!\n\n> **Example:** I'm **getting hungry**. I **haven't eaten since** 11 this morning.\n\n> **Example:** Why don't you go buy yourself a bag of potato chips or something?\n\n> **Example:** I might, but if I leave now, the concert **will have finished by the time** I come back.\n\n> **Example:** You're right. Let's wait for the food festival. Here, I brought some sweets in my purse.\n\n> **Example:** Oh, thanks.\n\n---\n\n***At the food and wine festival...***\n\n> **Example:** I've been to this food festival before, but this year it's **so much bigger**!\n\n> **Example:** Yeah, look at all the stands!\n\n> **Example:** We can **each either** buy 3 or 6 tickets for tastes of food. The tastes are small dishes of food, so you can try lots of different dishes.\n\n> **Example:** I'm **starving**. I could eat 20 dishes!\n\n> **Example:** I think I'll just buy 3. I **would eat 6 if I weren't** on a diet.\n\n> **Example:** Come on! You only live once. Enjoy yourself!\n\n> **Example:** I guess you're right. I'll buy 6 tickets!"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
