        {
          "code": 10025,
          "order": 3,
          "slug": {
            "es": "finding-work",
            "en": "finding-work"
          },
          "display": {
            "es": "Encontrando trabajo",
            "en": "Finding work"
          },
          "lecciones": [
            {
              "code": 216,
              "order": 1,
              "slug": {
                "es": "ways-to-find-a-job",
                "en": "ways-to-find-a-job"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "Maneras de encontrar trabajo",
                "en": "Ways to Find a Job"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "**1. Look on the internet for job postings.** Go to the websites that list job offers and allow you to post your résumé [C.V.].\n\nMirar anuncios de trabajo en internet. Acceder a páginas web que listen ofertas de trabajo y que le permitan publicar su currículum.\n\n**2. Mail or e-mail your C.V. to employers that interest you.**\n\nEnviar por correo o correo electrónico su currículum a empresas que le interesan.\n\n**3. Answer local newspaper or magazine ads.**\n\nContestar anuncios de trabajo de periódicos o revistas locales.\n\n**4. Go to employment agencies or search firms.**\n\nIr a agencias de empleo.\n\n**5. Ask family members, friends, teachers or professionals for job-leads.**\n\nPreguntar a familiares, amigos, profesores o profesionales por ofertas de trabajo.\n\n**6. Go personally to an office, factory or other employer that interests you**, introduce yourself and ask about job openings.\n\nIr personalmente a oficinas, fábricas u otros lugares de trabajo que le puedan interesar, presentarse y preguntar sobre posibles ofertas de trabajo.\n\n**7. Contacts, contacts, contacts!** Ask the people you know who are working in a company to inquire about job vacancies or to tell you the contact person that you should call or e-mail about job opportunities. Use your contacts' contacts to spread the word that you are looking for work.\n\n¡Contactos, contactos, contactos! Pregunte a la gente que conoce que esté trabajando en una empresa sobre los puestos vacantes o que le indiquen cuál es la persona de contacto a la que debe llamar o enviar un correo electrónico. Utilice los contactos de sus contactos para correr la voz de que Ud. está buscando trabajo.",
                "en": "**1. Look on the internet for job postings.** Go to the websites that list job offers and allow you to post your résumé [C.V.].\n\n**2. Mail or e-mail your C.V. to employers that interest you.**\n\n**3. Answer local newspaper or magazine ads.**\n\n**4. Go to employment agencies or search firms.**\n\n**5. Ask family members, friends, teachers or professionals for job-leads.**\n\n**6. Go personally to an office, factory or other employer that interests you**, introduce yourself and ask about job openings.\n\n**7. Contacts, contacts, contacts!** Ask the people you know who are working in a company to inquire about job vacancies or to tell you the contact person that you should call or e-mail about job opportunities. Use your contacts' contacts to spread the word that you are looking for work."
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 112,
              "order": 2,
              "slug": {
                "es": "curriculum-vitae",
                "en": "curriculum-vitae"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "Currículum Vitae",
                "en": "Curriculum Vitae"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "When we are writing our curriculum vitae, there a number of things we should include.\n\nCuando escribamos nuestro currículum vitae hay algunas cosas que deberíamos incluir.\n\n**1. Personal Information:** name, address, telephone number, email, etc.\n\nDatos personales:\n\nnombre, dirección, número de teléfono, correo electrónico...\n\n**2. Education and Qualifications:** your degree, university and/or completed studies\n\nEducación y calificaciones:\n\nsu título y Universidad o estudios que haya completado.\n\n**3. Professional Experience:** a list of jobs in chronological order, beginning with your current job\n\nExperiencia profesional:\n\nlistar los trabajos que haya tenido por orden cronológico con el puesto actual (o el más reciente) en primer lugar.\n\n**4. Skills:** languages, computer skills, organizational abilities, etc.\n\nHabilidades:\n\nidiomas, informática, capacidades organizativas, etc.\n\n> **Nota:** *Usar verbos de acción como “desarrollé”, “planeaba”, “organizaba”. Describir sus **habilidades**, \"trabajaba en equipo\", \"traté con tacto sobre las quejas de los clientes\", \"altamente organizado\", etc...*\n\n## Sample Curriculum Vitae (Ejemplo Currículum Vitae)\n\n**Suzanne Smith**<br>100 Sweet Lane<br>Townsville, FL<br>10000\n\nssmith@anemail.com<br>Mobile: 555-555-5555\n\n**__EDUCATION:__**\n\nBA in Tourism Management, June 2008<br>Florida International University\n\nMicrosoft Office Course, May - August 2006<br>Computer Courses International, Miami, FL\n\n**__PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE:__**\n\n**Travel Agent**, September 2010 - Present<br>Florida Family Vacation, Miami, FL<br>- Book vacations for families and international groups with adults and children<br>- Develop travel itineraries, working with partner companies and hotels to offer custom packages<br>- Design promotional materials and up-date the company website<br>- Train new staff in company policies and procedures\n\n**Hotel Receptionist**, June 2008 - August 2010<br>Sunny Hotel, Naples, FL<br>- Handled check-in and check-out of guests in a friendly manner<br>- Dealt with advanced reservations, took bookings and fulfilled particular requirements<br>- Operated the switchboard, messages and enquires<br>- Prepared the case for bank delivery at the end of the shift\n\n**Waitress**, June - August 2007<br>Fisherman's Catch Restaurant, Miami, FL<br>- Served customers in a friendly manner<br>- Explained the menu and the daily specials<br>- Served at special events of up to 200 guests<br>- Trained new wait staff\n\n**__LANGUAGES AND OTHER SKILLS:__**\n\n- Languages: English [native], Spanish [advanced], French [intermediate]<br>- Excellent customer service skills<br>- Highly skilled in Microsoft Office, Windows 98/XP, Expert Hotelier and website design\n\nSuzanne Smith\n\n100 Sweet Lane\n\nTownsville, FL\n\n10000\n\nssmith@anemail.com<br>Mobile: 555-555-5555\n\n**__EDUCACIÓN:__**\n\nLicenciatura en Turismo, junio 2008<br>Florida International University\n\nCurso de Microsoft Office, mayo - agosto 2006<br>Computer Courses International, Miami, FL\n\n**__EXPERIENCIA PROFESIONAL:__**\n\n- **Agente de viajes**, septiembre 2010 - actualidad: Florida Family Vacation, Miami, FL.<br>- Reserva de vacaciones para familias y grupos extranjeros de adultos y niños.<br>- Desarrollo de itinerarios de viaje trabajando con empresas colaboradoras y hoteles ofreciendo paquetes \"hechos a medida\".<br>- Diseño de materiales publicitarios y actualización de la página web.<br>- Formación de empleados nuevos en la política de la empresa y procedimientos.\n\n- **Recepcionista de hotel**, junio 2008 - agosto 2010: Sunny Hotel, Naples, FL.<br>- Gestión de los \"check-ins\" y \"check-outs\" de los huéspedes de una forma amable.<br>- Registro de las reservas incluyendo las anticipadas y realización de peticiones especiales para los clientes.<br>- Operadora de la centralita, toma de mensajes y respuesta a preguntas.<br>- Preparación del dinero en efectivo para la entrega al banco al final del turno.\n\n- **Camarera**, junio - agosto 2007: Fisherman's Catch Restaurant, Miami, FL.<br>- Atención y servicio a clientes en una manera amable y cordial.<br>- Explicación de la carta y los platos del día.<br>- Servicio en eventos especiales de hasta 200 clientes.<br>- Formación de nuevos empleados.\n\n**__IDIOMAS Y OTRAS CAPACIDADES:__**\n\n- Idiomas: Inglés [nativo], español [avanzado], francés [intermedio]<br>- Excelente trato con el cliente<br>- Muy capacitada en Microsoft Office, Windows 98/XP, Expert Hotelier y diseño de páginas web.",
                "en": "When we are writing our curriculum vitae, there a number of things we should include.\n\n**1. Personal Information:** name, address, telephone number, email, etc.\n\n**2. Education and Qualifications:** your degree, university and/or completed studies\n\n**3. Professional Experience:** a list of jobs in chronological order, beginning with your current job\n\n**4. Skills:** languages, computer skills, organizational abilities, etc.\n\n> **Note:** Be sure to use active verbs, such as \"**developed**,\" \"**planned**\" and \"**organized**\". Also include your skills, such as \"**working in a team**\", \"**tactfully dealing with complaining customers**,\" \"**highly organized**\", etc.\n\n## Sample Curriculum Vitae\n\n**Suzanne Smith**<br>100 Sweet Lane<br>Townsville, FL<br>10000\n\nssmith@anemail.com<br>Mobile: 555-555-5555\n\n**__EDUCATION:__**\n\nBA in Tourism Management, June 2008<br>Florida International University\n\nMicrosoft Office Course, May - August 2006<br>Computer Courses International, Miami, FL\n\n**__PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE:__**\n\n**Travel Agent**, September 2010 - Present<br>Florida Family Vacation, Miami, FL<br>- Book vacations for families and international groups with adults and children<br>- Develop travel itineraries, working with partner companies and hotels to offer custom packages<br>- Design promotional materials and up-date the company website<br>- Train new staff in company policies and procedures\n\n**Hotel Receptionist**, June 2008 - August 2010<br>Sunny Hotel, Naples, FL<br>- Handled check-in and check-out of guests in a friendly manner<br>- Dealt with advanced reservations, took bookings and fulfilled particular requirements<br>- Operated the switchboard, messages and enquires<br>- Prepared the case for bank delivery at the end of the shift\n\n**Waitress**, June - August 2007<br>Fisherman's Catch Restaurant, Miami, FL<br>- Served customers in a friendly manner<br>- Explained the menu and the daily specials<br>- Served at special events of up to 200 guests<br>- Trained new wait staff\n\n**__LANGUAGES AND OTHER SKILLS:__**\n\n- Languages: English [native], Spanish [advanced], French [intermediate]<br>- Excellent customer service skills<br>- Highly skilled in Microsoft Office, Windows 98/XP, Expert Hotelier and website design"
              }
            },
            {
              "code": 113,
              "order": 3,
              "slug": {
                "es": "interviews",
                "en": "interviews"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "Las entrevistas",
                "en": "Interviews"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "## Typical Interview Questions (Preguntas típicas en una entrevista)\n\n> **Example:** How would you describe yourself?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cómo se describiría a usted mismo?)\n\n> **Example:** What interests you about this position?\n> **Translation:** (¿Qué le interesa de este puesto?)\n\n> **Example:** Why did you choose this career?\n> **Translation:** (¿Por qué escogió esta carrera?)\n\n> **Example:** Explain what you did in your last job.\n> **Translation:** (Explíquenos lo que hacía en su último puesto de trabajo.)\n\n> **Example:** Why did you leave your last job?\n> **Translation:** (¿Por qué dejó su trabajo anterior?)\n\n> **Example:** Can you explain this gap in your employment history?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puede explicar este espacio vacío en su historial de empleo?)\n\n> **Example:** What do you see yourself doing five years from now?\n> **Translation:** (¿En qué puesto se ve usted dentro de cinco años?)\n\n> **Example:** Do you prefer working alone or in teams?\n> **Translation:** (¿Prefiere usted trabajar en solitario o en equipo?)\n\n> **Example:** How do you work under pressure?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cómo trabaja usted bajo presión?)\n\n> **Example:** What are you expectations regarding promotions and salary increases?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuáles son sus expectativas en lo que se refiere a ascensos y mejoras salariales?)\n\n> **Example:** What are your long-term career objectives?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuáles son sus objetivos profesionales a largo plazo?)\n\n> **Example:** Describe the best boss you ever had.\n> **Translation:** (Describa al mejor jefe que usted ha tenido.)\n\n> **Example:** Why should we hire you?\n> **Translation:** (¿Por qué deberíamos contratarle?)\n\n> **Example:** What qualifications do you have that would make you successful in this position?\n> **Translation:** (¿Qué aptitudes tiene usted que lo ayudarían a tener éxito en este puesto?)\n\n> **Example:** Have you ever been fired or forced to resign?\n> **Translation:** (¿Ha sido usted alguna vez despedido o forzado a renunciar?)\n\n> **Example:** Do you consider yourself a leader?\n> **Translation:** (¿Se considera a sí mismo un líder?)\n\n## Sample Interview (Ejemplo de una entrevista de trabajo)\n\n> **Example:** Mrs. Jones works at the Seaside Restaurant and is interviewing James for a waiter position.\n> **Translation:** <br>El Sra. Jones trabaja en el Seaside Restaurant y está entrevistando a James para un puesto de camarero.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Hello. Nice to meet you.\n> **Translation:** <br>Hola. Encantado de conocerlo.\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Hello. Yes, it's nice to meet you too.\n> **Translation:** <br>Hola. Sí, encantado igualmente.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Well, James, I have looked at your résumé and I wanted to ask you a few questions.\n> **Translation:** <br>bien, James, he mirado su currículum y quería formularle unas preguntas.\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, of course.\n> **Translation:** <br>Sí, por supuesto.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Please explain what you did in your last job and why you left.\n> **Translation:** <br>Explíqueme sus funciones en su último puesto de trabajo y ¿por qué lo dejó?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** I was working at Sam's Deli preparing sandwiches and other food orders for customers. I really enjoyed preparing the food, but what I liked most was the direct contact with the customers. When the summer season ended, my boss didn't need as much staff. Now I am looking for a position serving customers as a waiter.\n> **Translation:** <br>Estaba trabajando en Sam's Deli preparando bocadillos y otros platos para los clientes. Me gustaba preparar la comida pero lo que más me gustaba era el contacto directo con los clientes. Cuando la temporada de verano se acabó mi jefe no necesitaba tanto personal. Ahora estoy buscando un puesto de camarero sirviendo clientes directamente.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Did you serve people at tables at Sam's Deli or only prepare the food?\n> **Translation:** <br>¿Servías gente en las mesas en Sam's Deli o solo preparabas la comida?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Sometimes when we were short on wait staff I would serve customers at the tables.\n> **Translation:** <br>A veces cuando teníamos menos personal yo servía clientes en las mesas.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** What would your last boss say about you?\n> **Translation:** <br>¿Qué diría su último jefe sobre Ud.?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** I think he would say that I was a very hard worker, responsible and very friendly with everyone at the Deli.\n> **Translation:** <br>Creo que diría que soy muy trabajador, responsable y muy amable con todos en la Cafeteria.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** You also worked at a bakery a few summers ago. Tell me about that.\n> **Translation:** <br>También trabajó en una panadería hace unos veranos. Descríbamelo.\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I worked two summers in a row at the bakery. I had direct contact with the customers all day and I really enjoyed it.\n> **Translation:** <br>Sí, trabajé durante dos veranos seguidos en la panadería. Tuve contacto directo con los clientes todo el día y me gustó mucho.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** What about your studies? Are you still in school?\n> **Translation:** <br>¿Y los estudios? ¿Aún estás estudiando?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, this coming year will be my last year at university. I'm finishing my degree in Marketing.\n> **Translation:** <br>Sí, este año que viene será mi último año en la universidad. Estoy acabando mi licenciatura en Marketing.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** That's an interesting field. What hours are you available during the week and on the weekends?\n> **Translation:** <br>Ese es un interesante sector. ¿Qué horas tiene disponibles durante la semana y el fin de semana?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Starting on the 15th, I will be studying Monday to Friday in the mornings from 9:00 to 2:00 and I will be available to work anytime after 2:00. On Saturdays and Sundays I am available all day.\n> **Translation:** <br>Empezando el día 15, estaré estudiando de lunes a viernes por la mañana de 9:00 a 14:00 y estaré disponible para trabajar a cualquier hora a partir de las 14:00. Los sábados y domingos estoy disponible todo el día.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Good, we mostly need waiters for the dinner shift.\n> **Translation:** <br>Bien, sobre todo necesitamos camareros para el turno de la cena.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Tell me why you think I should hire you for this position.\n> **Translation:** <br>Dígame ¿por qué debería contratarle?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** I am a very responsible and hard-working person and I have really good customer service skills. I think I am a very friendly person and the customers will be happy with my service.\n> **Translation:** <br>Soy una persona muy responsable y trabajador y tengo muy buen trato con el cliente. Creo que soy una persona muy amable y que los clientes estarán contentos con mi servicio.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Well, it was great to meet you and I will be in touch in the next week about this position, ok?\n> **Translation:** <br>Bueno, ha sido un placer conocerlo y estaremos en contacto la próxima semana sobre este puesto, ¿vale?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, okay. Thank you very much.\n> **Translation:** <br>Sí, vale. Muchas gracias.",
                "en": "## Typical Interview Questions\n\n> **Example:** How would you describe yourself?\n\n> **Example:** What interests you about this position?\n\n> **Example:** Why did you choose this career?\n\n> **Example:** Explain what you did in your last job.\n\n> **Example:** Why did you leave your last job?\n\n> **Example:** Can you explain this gap in your employment history?\n\n> **Example:** What do you see yourself doing five years from now?\n\n> **Example:** Do you prefer working alone or in teams?\n\n> **Example:** How do you work under pressure?\n\n> **Example:** What are you expectations regarding promotions and salary increases?\n\n> **Example:** What are your long-term career objectives?\n\n> **Example:** Describe the best boss you ever had.\n\n> **Example:** Why should we hire you?\n\n> **Example:** What qualifications do you have that would make you successful in this position?\n\n> **Example:** Have you ever been fired or forced to resign?\n\n> **Example:** Do you consider yourself a leader?\n\n## Sample Interview\n\n> **Example:** Mrs. Jones works at the Seaside Restaurant and is interviewing James for a waiter position.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Hello. Nice to meet you.\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Hello. Yes, it's nice to meet you too.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Well, James, I have looked at your résumé and I wanted to ask you a few questions.\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, of course.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Please explain what you did in your last job and why you left.\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** I was working at Sam's Deli preparing sandwiches and other food orders for customers. I really enjoyed preparing the food, but what I liked most was the direct contact with the customers. When the summer season ended, my boss didn't need as much staff. Now I am looking for a position serving customers as a waiter.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Did you serve people at tables at Sam's Deli or only prepare the food?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Sometimes when we were short on wait staff I would serve customers at the tables.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** What would your last boss say about you?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** I think he would say that I was a very hard worker, responsible and very friendly with everyone at the Deli.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** You also worked at a bakery a few summers ago. Tell me about that.\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, I worked two summers in a row at the bakery. I had direct contact with the customers all day and I really enjoyed it.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** What about your studies? Are you still in school?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, this coming year will be my last year at university. I'm finishing my degree in Marketing.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** That's an interesting field. What hours are you available during the week and on the weekends?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Starting on the 15th, I will be studying Monday to Friday in the mornings from 9:00 to 2:00 and I will be available to work anytime after 2:00. On Saturdays and Sundays I am available all day.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Good, we mostly need waiters for the dinner shift.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Tell me why you think I should hire you for this position.\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** I am a very responsible and hard-working person and I have really good customer service skills. I think I am a very friendly person and the customers will be happy with my service.\n\n**Mrs. Jones:**\n\n> **Example:** Well, it was great to meet you and I will be in touch in the next week about this position, ok?\n\n**James:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, okay. Thank you very much."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "code": 10026,
          "order": 4,
          "slug": {
            "es": "money",
