              "view": {
                "es": "| Vocabulario |\n| --- |\n| hello<br>hola |\n| welcome<br>bienvenido |\n| good morning<br>buenos días |\n| good afternoon<br>buenas tardes |\n| good evening<br>buenas noches |\n| goodbye<br>adiós |\n| please<br>por favor |\n| thank you<br>gracias |\n| excuse me<br>perdón |\n| **Verbos** |\n| to meet<br>conocer |\n| to greet<br>saludar |\n\n## Useful Phrases (Frases útiles)\n\n> **Example:** What is your name?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cómo te llamas?)\n\n> **Example:** Hello, my name is...\n> **Translation:** (Hola, me llamo...)\n\n> **Example:** Pleased to meet you. / Nice to meet you.\n> **Translation:** (Encantado / Mucho gusto)\n\n> **Example:** How are you?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cómo estás?/¿Qué tal?)\n\n> **Example:** What's happening? / What's up?\n> **Translation:** (¿Qué pasa?)\n\n> **Example:** I'm fine, thank you.\n> **Translation:** (Estoy bien, gracias.)\n\n> **Example:** And you?\n> **Translation:** (¿Y tú?)\n\n> **Example:** How old are you?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuántos años tienes?)\n\n> **Example:** I am... years old.\n> **Translation:** (Tengo... años.)\n\n> **Example:** Where are you from?\n> **Translation:** (¿De dónde eres?)\n\n> **Example:** Where do you live?\n> **Translation:** (¿Dónde vives?)\n\n> **Example:** What do you do? / What do you do for a living?\n> **Translation:** (¿Qué haces? / ¿En qué trabajas?)\n\n> **Example:** Do you speak Spanish?\n> **Translation:** (¿Hablas español?)\n\n> **Example:** Excuse me.\n> **Translation:** (Perdón.)\n\n> **Example:** I don't understand.\n> **Translation:** (No entiendo.)\n\n> **Example:** Can you repeat, please?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puedes repetir por favor?)\n\n> **Example:** Can you speak slower, please?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puedes hablar más despacio por favor?)\n\n> **Example:** Thank you very much!\n> **Translation:** (¡Muchas gracias!)\n\n> **Example:** You're welcome.\n> **Translation:** (De nada.)\n\n> **Example:** See you later!\n> **Translation:** (¡Hasta luego!)\n\n> **Example:** Have a nice day!\n> **Translation:** (¡Que pase un buen día!)\n\n> **Example:** Same to you.\n> **Translation:** (Igualmente.)",
                "en": "### Vocabulary\n\n| English |\n| --- |\n| excuse me |\n| goodbye |\n| good afternoon |\n| good evening |\n| hello |\n| please |\n| thank you |\n| welcome |\n| **Verbs** |\n| to greet |\n| to meet |\n\n### Useful Phrases\n\n> **Example:** What is your name?\n\n> **Example:** Hello, my name is...\n\n> **Example:** Pleased to meet you. / Nice to meet you.\n\n> **Example:** How are you?\n\n> **Example:** What's happening? What's up?\n\n> **Example:** I'm fine, thank you.\n\n> **Example:** And you?\n\n> **Example:** How old are you?\n\n> **Example:** I am... years old.\n\n> **Example:** Where are you from?\n\n> **Example:** Where do you live?\n\n> **Example:** What do you do? / What do you do for a living?\n\n> **Example:** Do you speak Spanish?\n\n> **Example:** Excuse me.\n\n> **Example:** I don't understand.\n\n> **Example:** Can you repeat, please?\n\n> **Example:** Can you speak slower, please?\n\n> **Example:** Thank you very much!\n\n> **Example:** You're welcome.\n\n> **Example:** See you later!\n\n> **Example:** Have a nice day!\n\n> **Example:** Same to you."
              }
