              "view": {
                "es": "| Vocabulario |\n| --- |\n| airport<br>aeropuerto |\n| airplane<br>avión |\n| flight<br>vuelo |\n| boarding pass/card<br>tarjeta de embarque |\n| flight attendant (US), air hostess (UK), stewardess<br>azafata |\n| departure lounge/gate<br>sala de embarque |\n| check-in<br>facturación (del equipaje) |\n| round trip<br>ida y vuelta |\n| one way<br>ida |\n\n| Col 1 |\n| --- |\n| departures<br>salidas |\n| arrivals<br>llegadas |\n| layover<br>parada |\n| coach class<br>clase turista |\n| first class<br>primera clase |\n| business class<br>clase business |\n| luggage, baggage<br>equipaje |\n| suitcase<br>maleta |\n| carry on luggage/baggage<br>equipaje de mano |\n| customs<br>aduana |\n| **Verbos** |\n| to board<br>embarcar en |\n| to depart<br>salir |\n| to arrive<br>llegar |\n| to take off<br>despegar |\n| to land<br>aterrizar |\n\n## Useful Phrases (Frases útiles)\n\n> **Example:** Do you have your boarding pass?\n> **Translation:** (¿Tiene su tarjeta de embarque?)\n\n> **Example:** Do you have any baggage to check?\n> **Translation:** (¿Tiene equipaje para facturar?)\n\n> **Example:** Is there a layover?\n> **Translation:** (¿Hay una parada?)\n\n> **Example:** Only one carry on item is allowed.\n> **Translation:** (Sólo está permitido un artículo de mano.)\n\n> **Example:** Would you prefer a window or an aisle seat?\n> **Translation:** (¿Prefiere ventana o un asiento de pasillo?)\n\n> **Example:** Can you tell me where the departure gate is?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puede decirme dónde está la puerta de salida?)\n\n> **Example:** Can I see your passport, please?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puedo ver su pasaporte por favor?)\n\n> **Example:** I have nothing to declare.\n> **Translation:** (No tengo nada que declarar.)\n\n> **Example:** What is the purpose of your trip? Business or personal?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuál es el propósito de su viaje? ¿De negocios o personal?)\n\n> **Example:** What time is the plane boarding?\n> **Translation:** (¿A qué hora es el embarque del avión?)\n\n> **Example:** What time is the plane scheduled to take off [land]?\n> **Translation:** (¿A qué hora está previsto el avión para despegar (aterrizar)?)\n\n> **Example:** The flight is delayed/cancelled.\n> **Translation:** (El vuelo está retrasado/cancelado.)\n\n> **Example:** Where is the baggage claim?\n> **Translation:** (¿Dónde está la zona de recogida de equipaje?)\n\n> **Example:** I have lost my baggage.\n> **Translation:** (He perdido mi equipaje.)\n\n> **Example:** Have a nice flight!\n> **Translation:** (¡Que tenga un buen vuelo!)",
                "en": "### Vocabulary\n\n| English |\n| --- |\n| airport |\n| airplane |\n| aisle |\n| arrivals |\n| baggage |\n| baggage claim |\n| boarding pass/card |\n| business class |\n| carry on luggage/baggage |\n\n| Col 1 |\n| --- |\n| checked on luggage/baggage |\n| cancelled |\n| coach class |\n| customs |\n| delayed |\n| departure lounge/gate |\n| first class |\n| flight |\n| flight attendant (US), air hostess (UK), stewardess |\n| layover |\n| luggage |\n| one way |\n| passport |\n| round trip |\n| suitcase |\n| terminal |\n| visa |\n| window |\n| **Verbs** |\n| to arrive |\n| to board |\n| to check a bag |\n| to check-in |\n| to declare |\n| to depart |\n| to land |\n| to take off |\n\n### Useful Phrases\n\n> **Example:** Do you have your boarding pass?\n\n> **Example:** Do you have any baggage to check?\n\n> **Example:** Is there a layover?\n\n> **Example:** Only one carry on item is allowed.\n\n> **Example:** Would you prefer a window or an aisle seat?\n\n> **Example:** Can you tell me where the departure gate is?\n\n> **Example:** Can I see your passport, please?\n\n> **Example:** I have nothing to declare.\n\n> **Example:** What is the purpose of your trip? Business or personal?\n\n> **Example:** What time is the plane boarding?\n\n> **Example:** What time is the plane scheduled to take off [land]?\n\n> **Example:** The flight is delayed/cancelled.\n\n> **Example:** Where is the baggage claim?\n\n> **Example:** I have lost my baggage.\n\n> **Example:** Have a nice flight!"
              }
