              },
              "view": {
                "es": "| Vocabulario |\n| --- |\n| where<br>dónde |\n| map<br>mapa |\n| right<br>derecha |\n| left<br>izquierda |\n| straight<br>recto |\n| street, road<br>calle |\n| corner<br>esquina |\n| block<br>manzana |\n| bus<br>autobús |\n| train<br>tren |\n| subway, metro, underground/tube (UK)<br>metro |\n| taxi, cab<br>taxi |\n| fare<br>tarifa |\n| trip, journey<br>viaje |\n| stop<br>parada |\n| station<br>estación |\n| terminal<br>terminal |\n| ticket<br>billete |\n| transfer<br>transbordo |\n| opposite<br>enfrente de |\n| next to<br>al lado de |\n| across from<br>a través de |\n| behind<br>detrás de |\n| in front of<br>delante de |\n| **Verbos** |\n| to turn<br>girar, doblar |\n| to look for<br>buscar |\n| to be lost<br>estar perdido |\n| to help<br>ayudar |\n| to cross<br>cruzar, atravesar |\n| to catch, to take<br>tomar, coger |\n\n## Useful Phrases (Frases útiles)\n\n> **Example:** Where is...?\n> **Translation:** (¿Dónde está...?).\n\n> **Example:** Can you show me on the map?\n> **Translation:** (¿Me lo muestra en el mapa?)\n\n> **Example:** We are lost. Can you help us?\n> **Translation:** (Estamos perdidos. ¿Puede ayudarnos?)\n\n> **Example:** Which way do we go?\n> **Translation:** (¿Por dónde tenemos que ir?)\n\n> **Example:** Can you tell me the way to the metro?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puede decirme el camino para ir al metro?)\n\n> **Example:** Excuse me, can you tell me how to get to Main street, please?\n> **Translation:** (Disculpe, ¿Puede decirme cómo llegar a la calle Mayor, por favor?)\n\n> **Example:** Which way is the museum from here?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuál es el camino al museo desde aquí?)\n\n> **Example:** Turn right/left.\n> **Translation:** (Gire/doble a la derecha/izquierda.)\n\n> **Example:** When you arrive at the roundabout, take the first right.\n> **Translation:** (Cuando llegue a la rotonda, gire la primera a la derecha.)\n\n> **Example:** Go straight ahead.\n> **Translation:** (Siga recto.)\n\n> **Example:** I'm looking for...\n> **Translation:** (Busco....)\n\n> **Example:** Follow me!\n> **Translation:** (¡Sígueme!)\n\n> **Example:** Is there a bus stop near here?\n> **Translation:** (¿Hay una parada de autobús cerca de aquí?)\n\n> **Example:** It is next to/behind/in front of the supermarket.\n> **Translation:** (Está al lado/detrás de/delante del supermercado.)\n\n> **Example:** Do I have to transfer?\n> **Translation:** (¿Tengo que hacer transbordo?)\n\n> **Example:** What is the fare?\n> **Translation:** (¿Qué es la tarifa?)\n\n> **Example:** Where can I buy a token/ticket?\n> **Translation:** (¿Dónde puedo comprar una ficha/billete?)\n\n> **Example:** Where does this bus go?\n> **Translation:** (¿A dónde va este autobús?)\n\n> **Example:** What train line do I need to take?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuál linea tengo que tomar?)\n\n> **Example:** How far is it from here?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuanta distancia hay de aquí?)\n\n> **Example:** When does the next train leave?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuándo sale el proximo tren?)\n\n> **Example:** This is my seat.\n> **Translation:** (Este es mi asiento.)\n\n> **Example:** Please take me to the station.\n> **Translation:** (Por favor, lléveme a la estación.)\n\n> **Example:** Can you tell me when we get there?\n> **Translation:** (¿Me puede avisar cuando lleguemos?)\n\n> **Example:** Please let me off at the next corner.\n> **Translation:** (Por favor, déjeme en la próxima esquina.)\n\n> **Example:** Keep the change.\n> **Translation:** (Quédese con el cambio.)",
                "en": "### Vocabulary\n\n| English |\n| --- |\n| across |\n| behind |\n| block |\n| bus |\n| cab |\n| corner |\n| fare |\n| in front of |\n| journey |\n| left |\n| map |\n| metro |\n| next to |\n| opposite |\n| right |\n| road |\n| station |\n| stop |\n| straight |\n| street |\n| subway, metro, underground/tube (UK) |\n| taxi |\n| terminal |\n| ticket |\n| train |\n| transfer |\n| trip |\n| tube (UK) |\n| underground (UK) |\n| where |\n| **Verbs** |\n| to be lost |\n| to catch |\n| to cross |\n| to help |\n| to look for |\n| to turn |\n\n### Useful Phrases\n\n> **Example:** Where is...?\n\n> **Example:** Can you show me on the map?\n\n> **Example:** We are lost. Can you help us?\n\n> **Example:** Which way do we go?\n\n> **Example:** Can you tell me the way to the metro?\n\n> **Example:** Excuse me, can you tell me how to get to Main street, please?\n\n> **Example:** Which way is the museum from here?\n\n> **Example:** Turn right/left.\n\n> **Example:** When you arrive at the roundabout, take the first right.\n\n> **Example:** Go straight ahead.\n\n> **Example:** I'm looking for...\n\n> **Example:** Follow me!\n\n> **Example:** Is there a bus stop near here?\n\n> **Example:** It is next to/behind/in front of the supermarket.\n\n> **Example:** Do I have to transfer?\n\n> **Example:** What is the fare?\n\n> **Example:** Where can I buy a token/ticket?\n\n> **Example:** Where does this bus go?\n\n> **Example:** What train line do I need to take?\n\n> **Example:** How far is it from here?\n\n> **Example:** When does the next train leave?\n\n> **Example:** This is my seat.\n\n> **Example:** Please take me to the station.\n\n> **Example:** Can you tell me when we get there?\n\n> **Example:** Please let me off at the next corner.\n\n> **Example:** Keep the change."
              }
