              },
              "view": {
                "es": "| Vocabulario |\n| --- |\n| menu<br>carta, menú |\n| waiter, waitress<br>camarero, camarera |\n| bill, check<br>cuenta |\n| meal<br>comida |\n| breakfast<br>desayuno |\n| lunch<br>almuerzo, comida |\n| dinner<br>cena |\n| starter, appetizer<br>primer plato, entrante |\n| main course/dish<br>segundo plato, plato principal |\n| side dish<br>acompañamiento |\n| dessert<br>postre |\n| special(s)<br>plato del día |\n| specialties<br>especialidades |\n| house wine<br>vino de la casa |\n| vegetarian<br>vegetariano |\n| rare<br>poco hecho |\n| medium<br>al punto |\n| well done<br>muy hecho |\n| **Verbos** |\n| to order<br>pedir |\n| to serve<br>servir |\n\n## Useful Phrases (Frases útiles)\n\n> **Example:** How many in your party?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuántas personas hay en su grupo?)\n\n> **Example:** Table for 4, please.\n> **Translation:** (Una mesa para 4, por favor.)\n\n> **Example:** Do you have a reservation?\n> **Translation:** (¿Tiene una reserva?)\n\n> **Example:** May I see a menu, please?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puedo ver el menú, por favor?)\n\n> **Example:** What is today's special?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuál es el plato del día?)\n\n> **Example:** Are you ready to order?\n> **Translation:** (¿Está listo para pedir?)\n\n> **Example:** I am allergic to....\n> **Translation:** (Soy alérgico a...)\n\n> **Example:** Would you like something to drink?\n> **Translation:** (¿Le gustaría algo para beber?)\n\n> **Example:** How would you like your meat cooked? Well done, please.\n> **Translation:** (¿Cómo quiere su carne? Bien hecha, por favor.)\n\n> **Example:** Enjoy your meal!\n> **Translation:** (¡Buen provecho!)\n\n> **Example:** I'd like the check/bill, please\n> **Translation:** . (Me gustaría la cuenta, por favor.)",
                "en": "### Vocabulary\n\n| English |\n| --- |\n| appetizer |\n| bill |\n| breakfast |\n| check |\n| dessert |\n| dinner |\n| house wine |\n| lunch |\n| main course/dish |\n| meal |\n| medium |\n| menu |\n| rare |\n| side dish |\n| specialties |\n| special(s) |\n| starter |\n| vegetarian |\n| waiter,waitress |\n| well done |\n| **Verbs** |\n| to order |\n| to serve |\n\n### Useful Phrases\n\n> **Example:** How many in your party?\n\n> **Example:** Table for 4, please.\n\n> **Example:** Do you have a reservation?\n\n> **Example:** May I see a menu, please?\n\n> **Example:** What is today's special?\n\n> **Example:** Are you ready to order?\n\n> **Example:** I am allergic to....\n\n> **Example:** Would you like something to drink?\n\n> **Example:** How would you like your meat cooked? Well done, please.\n\n> **Example:** Enjoy your meal!\n\n> **Example:** I'd like the check/bill, please."
