              },
              "display": {
                "es": "Emergencias médicas",
                "en": "Medical Emergencies"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "| Vocabulario |\n| --- |\n| hospital<br>hospital |\n| ambulance<br>ambulancia |\n| emergency<br>emergencia |\n| doctor<br>médico, doctor |\n| nurse<br>enfermero/a |\n| pharmacy, chemist's (UK)<br>farmacia |\n| medicine<br>medicina |\n| prescription<br>receta |\n| insurance<br>seguro |\n| sick, ill<br>enfermo/a |\n| dizzy<br>mareado/a |\n| fever<br>fiebre |\n| flu<br>gripe |\n| virus<br>virus |\n| bacteria<br>bacteria |\n| germs<br>microbio |\n| diabetic<br>diabético |\n| nauseous<br>náusea |\n| blood pressure<br>presión arterial |\n| pulse<br>pulso |\n| headache<br>dolor de cabeza |\n| stomach ache<br>dolor de estómago |\n| sore throat<br>dolor de garganta |\n| diarrhea<br>diarrea |\n| cramps<br>calambres |\n| allergies<br>alergias |\n| heart attack<br>ataque al corazón/cardíaco |\n| serious<br>grave |\n| contagious<br>contagioso |\n| **Verbos** |\n| to hurt<br>doler |\n| to vomit<br>vomitar |\n| to fall<br>caerse |\n| to break<br>romper |\n| to be allergic to<br>ser alérgico |\n| to breathe<br>respirar |\n| to choke<br>ahogarse, asfixiarse |\n\n## Useful Phrases (Frases útiles)\n\n> **Example:** Help me!\n> **Translation:** (¡Ayúdame!)\n\n> **Example:** What's wrong?\n> **Translation:** (¿Qué pasa?)\n\n> **Example:** How do you feel?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cómo te sientes?)\n\n> **Example:** I don't feel well.\n> **Translation:** (No me siento bien.)\n\n> **Example:** I am sick.\n> **Translation:** (Estoy enfermo.)\n\n> **Example:** I need a doctor.\n> **Translation:** (Necesito un médico.)\n\n> **Example:** Call an ambulance!\n> **Translation:** (¡Llame a una ambulancia!)\n\n> **Example:** Where is the nearest hospital?\n> **Translation:** (¿Dónde está el hospital más cercano?)\n\n> **Example:** Do you have insurance?\n> **Translation:** (¿Tienes seguro?)\n\n> **Example:** I feel dizzy/nauseous.\n> **Translation:** (Me siento mareado/siento náuseas.)\n\n> **Example:** It hurts here.\n> **Translation:** (Me duele aquí.)\n\n> **Example:** I have a headache/stomach ache/sore throat/fever.\n> **Translation:** (Tengo dolor de cabeza/de estómago/de garganta/fiebre.)\n\n> **Example:** Can you give me something for...\n> **Translation:** (¿Me puede dar algo para...?)\n\n> **Example:** I am diabetic.\n> **Translation:** (Soy diabético.)\n\n> **Example:** Are you allergic to any medications?\n> **Translation:** (¿Eres alérgico a algún medicamento?)\n\n> **Example:** I am allergic to...\n> **Translation:** (Soy alérgico a...)\n\n> **Example:** I'm going to take your blood pressure.\n> **Translation:** (Voy a tomarte la presión.)\n\n> **Example:** I think I am going to vomit.\n> **Translation:** (Creo que voy a vomitar.)\n\n> **Example:** Is it serious/contagious?\n> **Translation:** (¿Es grave/contagioso?)\n\n> **Example:** Lie down!\n> **Translation:** (¡Acuéstese!)\n\n> **Example:** Breath!\n> **Translation:** (¡Respire!)\n\n> **Example:** Open your mouth!\n> **Translation:** (¡Abra la boca!)\n\n> **Example:** I need a prescription.\n> **Translation:** (Necesito una receta.)",
                "en": "### Vocabulary\n\n| English |\n| --- |\n| allergies |\n| ambulance |\n| bacteria |\n| blood pressure |\n| contagious |\n| cramps |\n| diabetic |\n| diarrhea |\n| dizzy |\n| doctor |\n| emergency |\n| fever |\n| flu |\n| germs |\n| headache |\n| heart attack |\n| hospital |\n| ill |\n| insurance |\n| medicine |\n| nauseous |\n| nurse |\n| pharmacy |\n| prescription |\n| pulse |\n| serious |\n| sick |\n| sore throat |\n| stomach ache |\n| virus |\n| **Verbs** |\n| to be allergic to |\n| to break |\n| to breathe |\n| to choke |\n| to fall |\n| to hurt |\n| to vomit |\n\n### Useful Phrases\n\n> **Example:** Help me!\n\n> **Example:** What's wrong?\n\n> **Example:** How do you feel?\n\n> **Example:** I don't feel well.\n\n> **Example:** I am sick.\n\n> **Example:** I need a doctor.\n\n> **Example:** Call an ambulance!\n\n> **Example:** Where is the nearest hospital?\n\n> **Example:** Do you have insurance?\n\n> **Example:** I feel dizzy/nauseous.\n\n> **Example:** It hurts here.\n\n> **Example:** I have a headache/stomach ache/sore throat/fever.\n\n> **Example:** Can you give me something for...\n\n> **Example:** I am diabetic.\n\n> **Example:** Are you allergic to any medications?\n\n> **Example:** I am allergic to...\n\n> **Example:** I'm going to take your blood pressure.\n\n> **Example:** I think I am going to vomit.\n\n> **Example:** Is it serious/contagious?\n\n> **Example:** Lie down!\n\n> **Example:** Breath!\n\n> **Example:** Open your mouth!\n\n> **Example:** I need a prescription."
