              "view": {
                "es": "| Vocabulario |\n| --- |\n| checkout, cashier, cash desk<br>caja |\n| sale(s)<br>rebajas |\n| salesperson (US), shop assistant (UK)<br>dependiente/a |\n| price-cut, discount<br>de oferta |\n| bargain<br>ocasión, ganga |\n| receipt<br>recibo |\n| clothing store<br>tienda de ropa |\n| shoe store<br>zapatería |\n| bookstore<br>librería |\n| department store<br>almacén |\n| supermarket, grocery store<br>supermercado |\n| jeweler<br>joyería |\n| toy store<br>juguetería |\n| news stand<br>quiosco |\n| size<br>talla, tamaño |\n| fitting/dressing rooms<br>probadores |\n| **Verbos** |\n| to look for<br>buscar |\n| to wrap<br>envolver |\n| to try on<br>probarse |\n\n### Useful Phrases (Frases útiles)\n\n> **Example:** Is there anything I can help you with?\n> **Translation:** (¿Hay algo en lo que pueda ayudarle?)\n\n> **Example:** I'm just looking, thanks.\n> **Translation:** (Sólo estoy mirando, gracias.)\n\n> **Example:** Can you please help me?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puede ayudarme?)\n\n> **Example:** I'm looking for...\n> **Translation:** (Estoy buscando...)\n\n> **Example:** How much is it?\n> **Translation:** (¿Cuánto cuesta?)\n\n> **Example:** I'll take it.\n> **Translation:** (Me lo quedo.)\n\n> **Example:** What is it made of?\n> **Translation:** (¿De qué material es?)\n\n> **Example:** How late are you open?\n> **Translation:** (¿Hasta cuándo está abierto?)\n\n> **Example:** What time do you close?\n> **Translation:** (¿A qué hora cierra?)\n\n> **Example:** May I try it on, please?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puedo probarmelo por favor?)\n\n> **Example:** Where are the fitting rooms?\n> **Translation:** (¿Dónde están los probadores?)\n\n> **Example:** What size is it?\n> **Translation:** (¿Qué talla es?)\n\n> **Example:** It's too big/small.\n> **Translation:** (Es demasiado grande/pequeño.)\n\n> **Example:** Do you have a smaller/larger size?\n> **Translation:** (¿Tiene una talla más pequeña/grande?)\n\n> **Example:** Do you accept credit cards?\n> **Translation:** (¿Acepta tarjetas de crédito?)\n\n> **Example:** Can I have a bag?\n> **Translation:** (¿Tiene una bolsa?)\n\n> **Example:** Can you please gift wrap it?\n> **Translation:** (¿Podría envolverlo en papel de regalo por favor?)\n\n> **Example:** The receipt, please.\n> **Translation:** (El recibo por favor.)\n\n> **Example:** Can you ship it?\n> **Translation:** (¿Puede enviarlo?)\n\n> **Example:** That's all, thanks.\n> **Translation:** (Eso es todo, gracias.).",
                "en": "### Vocabulary\n\n| English |\n| --- |\n| bargain |\n| bookstore |\n| checkout, cashier, cash desk |\n| clothing store |\n| department store |\n| fitting/dressing rooms |\n| grocery store |\n| jeweler |\n| newsstand |\n| price-cut, discount |\n| receipt |\n| sale(s) |\n| salesperson (US), shop assistant (UK) |\n| shoe store |\n| size |\n| grocery store |\n| toy store |\n| **Verbs** |\n| to look for |\n| to try on |\n| to wrap |\n\n### Useful Phrases\n\n> **Example:** Is there anything I can help you with?\n\n> **Example:** I'm just looking, thanks.\n\n> **Example:** Can you please help me?\n\n> **Example:** I'm looking for...\n\n> **Example:** How much is it?\n\n> **Example:** I'll take it.\n\n> **Example:** What is it made of?\n\n> **Example:** How late are you open?\n\n> **Example:** What time do you close?\n\n> **Example:** May I try it on, please?\n\n> **Example:** Where are the fitting rooms?\n\n> **Example:** What size is it?\n\n> **Example:** It's too big/small.\n\n> **Example:** Do you have a smaller/larger size?\n\n> **Example:** Do you accept credit cards?\n\n> **Example:** Can I have a bag?\n\n> **Example:** Can you please gift wrap it?\n\n> **Example:** The receipt, please.\n\n> **Example:** Can you ship it?\n\n> **Example:** That's all, thanks."
              }
