            {
              "code": 217,
              "order": 2,
              "slug": {
                "es": "clothing-shop-assistant",
                "en": "clothing-shop-assistant"
              },
              "display": {
                "es": "Dependiente de una tienda de ropa",
                "en": "Clothing Shop Assistant"
              },
              "view": {
                "es": "| Vocabulario |\n| --- |\n| blouse<br>blusa |\n| boots<br>botas |\n| cotton<br>algodón |\n| dress<br>vestido |\n| fitting rooms<br>probadores |\n| hanger<br>colgador |\n| high-heeled shoes<br>zapatos de tacón |\n| jacket<br>chaqueta |\n| jeans<br>vaqueros |\n| on sale<br>rebajado |\n| linen<br>lino |\n| pants<br>pantalones |\n| purse<br>bolso (de mujer) |\n| sales<br>rebajas |\n| sandals<br>sandalias |\n| shirt<br>camisa |\n| silk<br>seda |\n| size<br>talla |\n| shoes<br>zapatos |\n| shorts<br>pantalones cortos |\n| skirt<br>falda |\n| suit<br>traje |\n| sweater<br>jersey |\n| too big<br>demasiado grande |\n| too small<br>demasiado pequeño |\n| trousers<br>pantalones |\n| t-shirt<br>camiseta |\n| vest<br>chaleco |\n| wallet<br>cartera/monedero |\n| wool<br>lana |\n\n## Useful expressions (Frases útiles)\n\n> **Example:** Hello. Can I help you find something?\n> **Translation:** (Hola. ¿Puedo ayudarle a encontrar lo que busca?)\n\n> **Example:** What size are you?\n> **Translation:** (¿Qué talla gastas?)\n\n> **Example:** Would you like to try this dress on?\n> **Translation:** (¿Quiere probarse este vestido?)\n\n> **Example:** The fitting rooms are here.\n> **Translation:** (Aquí están los probadores.)\n\n> **Example:** Would you like me to get you a different size?\n> **Translation:** (¿Quiere que le traiga otra talla?)\n\n> **Example:** We have them in lots of different colors.\n> **Translation:** (Los tenemos en muchos diferentes colores.)\n\n> **Example:** You can pay with cash or credit card.\n> **Translation:** (Puede pagar en efectivo o con tarjeta de crédito.)\n\n## Dialogue in a Clothing Shop (Diálogo en una tienda de ropa)\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Good morning. Can I help you?\n> **Translation:** <br>Buenos días. ¿Puedo ayudarle?\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** No, thanks. I'm just looking.\n> **Translation:** <br>No, gracias. Solo estoy mirando.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Hi. Can I help you find something?\n> **Translation:** <br>Hola. ¿Puedo ayudarle a encontrar algo?\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes. Do you have this t-shirt in white?\n> **Translation:** <br>Sí. ¿Tienen esta camiseta en blanco?\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, here they are. What size are you?\n> **Translation:** <br>Sí, aquí están. ¿Qué talla gasta?\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Medium.\n> **Translation:** <br>Mediana.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Here you go.\n> **Translation:** <br>Aquí tiene.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Thank you.\n> **Translation:** <br>Gracias.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** We also have these t-shirts in white.\n> **Translation:** <br>También tenemos estas camisetas en blanco.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Oh, yes. I like them. How much are they?\n> **Translation:** <br>Me gustan. ¿Cuánto cuestan?\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** 9 euros.\n> **Translation:** <br>9 euros.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Okay, I will try them both on.\n> **Translation:** <br>Vale, me las probaré las dos.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** The fitting rooms are here.\n> **Translation:** <br>Aquí están los probadores.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Thank you.\n> **Translation:** <br>Gracias\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** How do they look on you?\n> **Translation:** <br>¿Cómo le quedan?\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** I like them both. And since I wear lots of t-shirts, I will take both of them.\n> **Translation:** <br>Me gustan las dos. Y como me pongo muchas camisetas, me llevo las dos.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Great.\n> **Translation:** <br>Muy bien.\n\n__**At the cash register (en la caja)**__\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** That will be 16,95, please.\n> **Translation:** <br>Serán 16,95, por favor.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Can I pay with a credit card?\n> **Translation:** <br>¿Puedo pagar con tarjeta de crédito?\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, of course.\n> **Translation:** <br>Sí, claro/por supuesto.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** You can enter your pin now.\n> **Translation:** <br>Puedes entrar tu número pin ahora.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Okay.\n> **Translation:** <br>Vale.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Thanks very much. Come again.\n> **Translation:** <br>Muchas gracias. Vuelve otro día.\n\n**Costumer:**\n\n> **Example:** Okay. Bye-bye.\n> **Translation:** <br>Vale. Adiós.",
                "en": "| Vocabulary |\n| --- |\n| blouse |\n| boots |\n| cotton |\n| dress |\n| fitting rooms |\n| hanger |\n| high-heeled shoes |\n| jacket |\n| jeans |\n| on sale |\n| linen |\n| pants |\n| purse |\n| sales |\n| sandals |\n| shirt |\n| silk |\n| size |\n| shoes |\n| shorts |\n| skirt |\n| suit |\n| sweater |\n| too big |\n| too small |\n| trousers |\n| t-shirt |\n| vest |\n| wallet |\n| wool |\n\n## Useful expressions\n\n> **Example:** Hello. Can I help you find something?\n\n> **Example:** What size are you?\n\n> **Example:** Would you like to try this dress on?\n\n> **Example:** The fitting rooms are here.\n\n> **Example:** Would you like me to get you a different size?\n\n> **Example:** We have them in lots of different colors.\n\n> **Example:** You can pay with cash or credit card.\n\n## Dialogue in a Clothing Shop\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Good morning. Can I help you?\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** No, thanks. I'm just looking.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Hi. Can I help you find something?\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes. Do you have this t-shirt in white?\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, here they are. What size are you?\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Medium.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Here you go.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Thank you.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** We also have these t-shirts in white.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Oh, yes. I like them. How much are they?\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** 9 euros.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Okay, I will try them both on.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** The fitting rooms are here.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Thank you.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** How do they look on you?\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** I like them both. And since I wear lots of t-shirts, I will take both of them.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Great.\n\n__**At the cash register**__\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** That will be 16,95, please.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Can I pay with a credit card?\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Yes, of course.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** You can enter your pin now.\n\n**Customer:**\n\n> **Example:** Okay.\n\n**Shop assistant:**\n\n> **Example:** Thanks very much. Come again.\n\n**Costumer:**\n\n> **Example:** Okay. Bye-bye."
              }
